# Cursor Rules

## Coding Standards
- Follow PEP 8 style guidelines for Python code
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add docstrings to all functions and classes
- Keep functions small and focused on a single task

## Project Structure
- All source code must be placed in the src directory
- Organize code into appropriate modules and packages within src
- Keep related code in the same module
- Use appropriate design patterns
- Maintain separation of concerns

## Environment Management
- Always use virtual environment (.venv) for the project
- Document all dependencies in requirements.txt
- Use pip install -r requirements.txt for installing dependencies
- For GUI applications, use PyQt as the default framework
